Me: Got it.

Facilyn: Let’s begin with the decision-makers.

Facilyn: For now, do you want to focus on just yourself?

Facilyn: Or should we expand the “whole” — include anyone you live with, decide with, or who can veto your choices?

- #decision_makers

@dmkrs_explanation
title: What difference does it make?
max-visits: 1
order: 21
tags: decision_makers

Me: What difference does it make?

Facilyn: If you leave out people who have veto power, you invite conflict.

A faint whirring passes outside, then the wind rattles the teahouse sign again.

Both of you glance toward the window.

A postal robot is attempting to deliver mail to a fire hydrant. It adjusts its angle, retries, then waits politely — convinced the hydrant is simply a quiet resident.

Facilyn watches it for a moment.

Facilyn: See?

Facilyn: The system thinks it has the right address. The hydrant disagrees.

She looks back at you.

Facilyn: Exclude a real stakeholder, and you end up negotiating with a fire hydrant.

- #decision_makers

@dmkrs_me
title: Just me.
